Oumaïma Belahbib (nke a na-akpọkwa Oumayma, amụrụ n'abalị iri abụọ na otu n'ọnwa Ọgọstụ n'afọ 1996) bụ onye Morocco na-akụ ọkpọ, onye ritere ihe nrite ọla edo na 2017 African Amateur Boxing Championships, na ọla nchara na 2019 African Games. O sonyere na ihe omume welterweight (n'okpuru 69 kg) na 2020 Summer Olympics.

Na 2017 African Amateur Boxing Championships na Brazzaville, Congo, Belahbib meriri ihe omume na-erubeghị kilogram 64. Ọ bụ ihe nrite ọla edo mbụ nke ụmụ nwanyị Morocco na African Amateur Boxing Championships, na naanị ihe nrite ego ha nke 2017 Championships. O ritere ọla nchara n'ihe omume na-erubeghị kilogram 69 na 2019 African Games. Ka e mesịrị n'afọ ahụ, ọ sonyeere na 2019 AIBA Women's World Boxing Championships, na-emeri Lovlina Borgohain nke India na agba nke iri na isii.

Na Jenụwarị 2020, o ritere ọla nchara na asọmpi mba ụwa nke Nations Cup, na Febụwarị 2020, Belahbib meriri asọmpi asọmpi asọmpụ nke African Boxing Olympic Qualification nke afọ 2020 n'okpuru 69 kilogram. N'ihi ya, ọ ruru eru maka ihe omume welterweight (n'okpuru 69 kg) na 2020 Summer Olympics. E mesiri ya obi ike n'ọnọdụ ya n'egwuregwu ahụ mgbe o meriri onye Kenya Elizabeth Akinyi na ọkara ikpeazụ ya. N'afọ 2021, o ritere ọla nchara ọzọ na asọmpi mba ụwa nke Nations Cup. Na 2020 Olympics, Belahbib meriri onye Ukraine Anna Lysenko n'egwuregwu nke iri na isii.
